reviews:
Really small room. And without any view except the wall vis-a-vis. But it’s very clean and the stuff is friendly! The location nearby the metro 6 and 7 is perfect to reach all important sights.
On the whole it’s ok for a small budget and less claims.

Mixed feelings about it.
Rooms are much smaller than they appear on the websites but linen is perfect white and fresh. Matress is very comfortable. Bathroom layout works but keep in mind is tiny in size, though clean and with fluffy white towels.
A/C is said to be controlled by front desk but we had no ventilation nor cool air flowing, therefore we opted to leave the window open.
Location is fabulous to explore Paris with Metro Station and Bus stop within 3min walk. Lots of eateries and bars around for a late night snack and drinks.
Special thanks to Night front desk staff, we were kindly received after hours.
If you are on a budget, it works out... Just keep in mind comfort will be sacrificed a bit.

I enjoyed my stay. The hotel is very clean and modern. Front desk were polite, friendly and all spoke English well enough to answer any questions or give directions. I would stay there again. In fact, I will.

This was a great base to attend a conference nearby. The staff were really friendly and helpful and our room was very nice albeit with slightly restricted ceiling height on one side because it was up at the top of the building. The bathroom was large and had a bath which was a bonus. The hotel was very clean and the wifi was good. The buffet breakfast was nice and was perfectly adequate for the price. There was plenty of room to sit downstairs whilst waiting to go out. It looked as if it might be possible to buy drinks from a bar area but we didn't see anyone doing so. The area round the hotel was nice with plenty of places to eat and the Metro was very close by. We would happily stay there again.

We can only recommend this nice little hotel where we were kindly welcomed. Good transportation options (bus, metro), close to Orly airport (20-30 minutes by taxi, Orly bus stop is also close by metro), and nice restaurants nearby.
We had a small, but comfortable room with everything we needed.

The kindness of the staff is excellent, This is good place to stay in Paris- Transports from and to hotel are comfortable. The Rooms are clean and medium large. The distance from classical places is acceptable

This hotel is clean and well organised, while also having a cozy ambience. The beds are comfortable, the bathrooms are modern, the staff is friendly. The price is very competitive for this level of quality.

We wanted a hotel near place d'Italie. Location of the hotel is perfect. Staff is great. As usual in Paris, the room is tiny which was a disappointment considering the price. In addition, there was a carpet which is far from easy to clean in a perfect way regarding the size of the room....

+ Clean rooms
+ Stable WiFi
+ Good access to public transport
+ Several restaurants and shopping opportunities nearby
+ Very friendly and helpful reception
+ Calm during the nights

- Bathroom had a bit of smell

Nice hotel, clean and nice balcony, good localisation close to a big subway station, good connection and very nice welcome. It was a very good stay and I recommend this hotel in Paris. Very nice and good price.

Lovely stay in a very comfortable hotel which is well placed for the Metro. Nice a quiet at night despite being well placed for restaurants etc.. Helpful staff along with a good continental breakfast. My 13 year old daughter and I enjoyed our stay and would come back again.

Everything met or even exceeded our expectations. A very pleasant stay. Good location, nice staff, good rooms, good breakfast. If we are back n Paris, we will gladly take the Hotel La Manufakctur again.

I had a standard room in the first floor. Relatively small and some refurbishment would be needed. The safe did not work. The windows are basic and street noise is clearly audible in the room; however, the hotel is located at a street that is quiet at night. The room and bathroom were clean, the bed was comfortable. Breakfast buffet offered a good (albeit not outstanding) selection in terms of both, quality and choice. The reception hall is recently renovated and quite nice. Close to the metro (Place d'Italie) and in one of my favourite Paris neighbourhoods (not very touristic). Overall, not splendid but considering the relatively low price to pay, still a good deal. I was satisfied.

the hotel location is perfect, right outside the metro and has lots of restaurants to eat at nearby. The hotel is very welcoming and comfortable. The rooms sre extremely clean, lovely and the beds are lovely too. The breakfast is a continental buffet which was delicious. Overall this hotel is perfect, I would definitely stay here or recommend it here.

Superb hotel and very professional staff. Ideally situated as located only one minute from bus stop and metro. 20 minutes from Quartier Latin. Quiet hotel and very good quality and services for a 3 star hotel. I will definitely come back here for my next stay.

Very friendly staff.
When i arrived hotel i felt very welcomed from the staff.

Clean room with safe access in & out of hotel.
Restaurants & supermarkets are a lot around hotel

i would like to stay again in case needed.

Small, comfortable, well situated hotel in an old house, very friendly helpful service, the room was very small but very clean. If you plan to see Paris and stay outside for sight seeing the hotel is a perfect choice!

Fantastic location surrounded by cute cafes and restaurants. The room was incredibly clean, but small... which I think is a given in Paris. One of the most comfortable beds I have ever slept on. The staff were helpful in navigating the train disruptions caused by the protests.

Great little hotel near Place d'Italie. It feels more like a good two-star hotel than a three-star one (no mineral or filtered water in the rooms, for example), but an obvious effort is made on keeping prices down. So as a whole, I'll give it maximum rating, not because it's the best 3 star I've ever stayed in, but because it's an excellent package: quiet, good breakfast at the price, excellent value, generally sweet.
For people who don't know Paris, Place d'Italie is right between the 13th arrondissement (not sexy at all) and the 5th (very sexy). It's not central per se, but neither is it remote. You can easily walk into the the 5th. You would pay 60 or 70%more for the same hotel in the 6th arrondissement, for example.
Reccommended.

The hotel is very close to Place d'Italie, where there is also a shopping center, in a very quiet street. I found the room very comfortable with special attention to the guest.
Breakfast is not included but in the room there is the necessary to prepare coffee or tea.

A small but well-run hotel, in a clean and quiet location, not too far from the city center. A shopping mall is also within 15 minutes walk. Their building is adjacent to a big police building, felt pretty safe in the evening.

The staff are very friendly and speak good English. They offer to hold our luggages even after checkout We booked a family room which became a good surprise. Love the layout—two corner rooms adjacent to each other with a share entrance. It felt like a small 2 bedrooms apartment, each has its own bathroom. Perfect for family with grownup kids.

Did not try their breakfast, can not comment on it. There are several other restaurants within 3-5 minutes walk. A small Carrefour store just cross street. They have hot pizza in the morning.

We will definitely return for our next visit to Paris.

We spent several days at the hotel straddling the New Year, as a family of nine, ranging from grandparents to our youngest grandchild aged 7. We took advice from the booking staff regarding detailed room bookings and the rooms met our needs in every way. We took a combination of intercommunicating and free standing bedrooms, all of which were well maintained and fitted out with all necessary fittings. The reception staff could not have been more helpful and we were impressed by the high standard of cleanliness throughout. The breakfast was a nice continental buffet and the hotel is well situated with nice areas and good restaurants nearby and very easy and convenient bus and/or metro connections to other parts of central Paris. We had a most enjoyable stay and will not hesitate to return.

A clean and comfortable hotel. The staff is friendly. The location is not central, but seems safe and in 25 minutes by public transportation to Eiffel tower. I can only recommend the hotel. Especially given the price (honestly, the hotel could cost twice as much as...)

Polite, friendly and professional staff. Rooms were clean and tidy. Ease of access to Bus and Metro (Place d'italie). Great location to explore. Enjoyed my stay and i am happy and will highly recommend the hotel to friends.

Consistently good - have stayed several times over the years and never been disappointed. Rooms are of reasonable size, comfortable and quiet with choice of balconies in some rooms which is nice in the summer time.

In Paris Centre, near Porte d 'Ítaly with good metro connections. this hotel is an excellent place to explore Paris. The hotel has small, but well designed rooms with comfortable bed. Nice to have coffee and tea at hand and a writing desk to work at the laptop..

Hotel had a good location, not too far from landmarks. the breakfast wasnt that great. no much options.and the croissants were small. but the taste was good.
Overall i enjoyed my stay and i am happy and will surely recommend the hotel to friends.

excellentlocation, close to Metro and RER, also close to BP and easy to find. Very safe place, calm and convenient. Perfect breakfast, very friendly hotel staff, rooms are small but all is in place - nothing missed. Can highly recommend, for Paris an excellent choice

The property is beautifully located just off an archetypal, picture postcard, leafy, wide boulevard. Delightful cafes nearby and excellent access to transport. Scrupulously clean. Pleasant breakfast area.
What impressed us most was the customer service - above and beyond and a rarity in Paris.
We had an issue but it was resolved to our satisfaction impressively quickly.
Highly, highly recommended

Once again, we had a wonderful stay here. The staff is friendly, attentive, and accommodating. The room was clean and comfortable. The location has great metro and bus access to anywhere in the Paris Metro area. Plus wonderful inexpensive restaurants, stores, and movie theaters.

Not great quick stop before heading to paris
Small room could use a bit if updating parking a few blocks away hard to find on streets had to put car in lot overnight
Friendly front desk staff but a bit pricey for what it is could use an upgrade to justify price

Excellent accommodation. Friendly and helpful staff. Wide selection for the buffet breakfast. Very handy location for public transport. Hotel were very good at communicating and offering directions and advice. Reasonably priced. Really enjoyed our stay

The hotel is very well located. There are many nice restaurants around it. The rooms are very clean. Florent, Cylia, Geoffroy and all other staff are verykind and friendly. It was our first time to visit Paris and we really enjoyed staying at this hotel and strongly recomment it to those for business and family trips.

The hotel is very close to the train station that takes you everywhere. The room is so charming and clean. We had two rooms together with a connecting door for our family of 4. Both rooms had balcony with a great view. We even had breakfast in the balcony. The staff was very nice and caring. Coming back to Paris we will stay here again.

We ended up here when our original booking cancelled on us. This was one of the last rooms in Paris available that night which happened to be a major soccer tournament. We got a small room but it was nice and the bathroom was fine. I would recommend going for a larger room. The staff was extraordinarily kind to us as we ended up extending our stay due to COVID. They were super helpful and made the quarantine as comfortable as possible. We didn't get to enjoy the amenities much (a lot of UberEats for us) but the hotel looked lovely.

The hotel is very well located, the accommodations are clean and in good standing. The room was nice and very clean and the bed was comfortable.

The team was very kind and nice and always happy to help if needed.

I recommend this hotel. Thanks !

We recently visited Paris and had a fantastic time taking in all the sites am enjoying their fabulous Bastille Day.

We stayed at the Hotel du Bois and you could not find a better location.

It is listed as a 3 star hotel but wow the staff offer a five star service, all the staff were kind , friendly and very patient.

Zahir and all the reception staff were wonderful as was Munya the lady who did the breakfast such a warm genuine lady.

We went with our granddaughter Lucy and she said it was the trip of a lifetime.

We will certainly visit again and when we do we will choose the hotel du bois.

Thanks to everyone for looking after us so well.

Catherine,Stephen and Lucy room 114, really nice triple room. Stay from the 7th-14th of July inclusive x

I am so glad to pay a premium for a balcony view in this hotel. Perfect way to immerse in French culture with staying in this classic hotel with balcony. Yet the room is relatively small but it is still valuable and close to metro station.

We stayed for 1 night in June 2022. Overall a small boutique hotel
Positives:
Excellent location - very close to a shopping mall and a very busy metro station (with multiple metro lines). Also lots of F&B options / supermarkets nearby
Helpful staff - Staff was courteous and answered all our queries. They were also gracious to change our room when we requested a change due to the size of the room
Good facilities - All rooms have a safety locker / hot water kettle (not common in Paris), spacious elevators (helpful to carry luggage upstairs)

Negatives:
The room allotted to us (Room 1 on first floor) was very small. Upon our request our room was changed to Room 2 (next room) which was only (very slightly) bigger than Room 1 but had a limitation of broken window which could not be opened. We were OK since we didn't intend to open the windows anyways (being on first floor and views of an internal lane). Not sure of how the other rooms in the hotel are

1. Location strategically located near train station.
2. Room was clean albeit a little bit small.
3. Comfortable for two person
5. Staff was friendly n helpful.
6. Breakfast was available with cost.
7. Should provide more chaging port for handphone

Friendly and helpful staff; hotel in a quiet area with nice cafes and restaurants within a short walking distance. Recommend the Jules restaurant for their onion soup. Breakfast was adequate but would have preferred espresso and not just coffee.

we spent 3 nights in a simple but very comfortable room. It was very nicely equipped and clean. The view wasn't the best but the window besides the bed was beautiful and let quite a lot of light in, which we loved. The location of the hotel was great - the area is very well connected with the metro and has quite a lot of small cafés and breakfast places around. Overall it was a lovely stay and perfect for a weekend trip to Paris. We might come back!

It was an Excellent stay, a very good location, with very good services an breakfast and helpful staff.
I would definitely come again and I highly recommend this hotel for staying in Paris with your family.

I had a double room without balcony. Coming from the US or other smaller town the room for two might feel small, but is much spacious with respect to standard Paris double rooms. Excellent stay. Lovely staff. Reasonably priced European breakfast = way better than fancy hotels in the US. I would still recommend skip breakfast and get crêpes or pastries somewhere else.

Windows in my room were essentially like balconies. Definitely had phone calls sitting on the ledge.

The hotel is located in lovely, lively, gorgeous area. It is also secure being right next to the police station. There are various metro and bus lines facilitating movement. The stuff is very friendly, all time available and very attentive (aux petits soins) and the hotel is so clean. My room was very comfortable and cosy. The view is alo lovely and my overall journey was memorable thanks to the hotel stuff and the nice place. I highly recommend La Manufacture, keep up the good work. It was my first but absolutely not my last visit.

Hotel was in a great location, close to the metro to easily access different parts of the city.
The bed was very comfortable and the room was spacious.
Staff was very friendly and helpful in making recommendations for restaurants nearby.
We would be happy to return to this hotel.

Nice hotel with very friendly and helpful staff. Perfect for a short stayover in a good location in walking distance from the Latin Quarter and just next to Place D'Italie, which connects many Metro lines.

This was my first trip to Paris in many years that was not for business. I was looking for a hotel that was clean, efficient, well located but not too expensive. I knew i could not stay in the centre as I had on business, and so had to add a little travelling time, but the variety of services and destinations from Place d'Italie 50 yards away is excellent, and I chose the hotel frmo the internet. The staff, especially in reception, were personable, cheerful and helpful, especially so when, at the booking stage, there was a confusion about the payment. The room was very clean and I was lucky to be upgraded which was a bonus. Breakfast had everything I wanted. I would certainly recommend the hotel. The lights in the breakfast room are however placed too low for somebody over 1m90 and have sharp metal lower elements that hurt when encountered on trying to make way for another guest.

Decent location close to several metro stations and easily walkable around the city. Safe, very cute neighbourhood and things around. Room was fine. Comfortable beds, good shower. Not spacious but not cramped. Size wise a good base if you're planning to be out and about most of the time.

Issue was the noise- both inside and out. All cities are loud but having double glazed windows would helped the external noise. Internal noise- wow that was what actually woke me up. First of all the chamber cleaners woke me up my incessently knocking and then attempting to enter my room at 8am on a Sunday WHEN I HAD THE DO NOT DISTURB SIGN HANGING FROM THE DOOR. They then proceeded to speak loudly to each other in the hallways and when servicing rooms around me, clean as though the directive had been "make as much noise as possible" banging into the wall, kncoking into things. all before 9am on a weekend. It's the first time I haven't left a tip for the cleaners.

Furniture should be improved and carpets removed.
One should not walk in rooms without wearing shoes.
Otherwise, comfy despite insuffisient room for organizing personal stuff.
Extremely safe as directly if front of a huge police station.

Very comfortable and well appointed room. A tad small for two people, stepping around each other and the balcony didn't have a view but otherwise great. Very convenient to be located very close to a main metro station. Pleasant circle with access to cafes and restaurants. Friendly and attentive front desk staff. Just hope the cleaning staff are kind enough to return the gold ring I lost.

We stayed four nights, everything was good, clean room, very comfortable bed, fantastic location, three metro lines in less than 500 meters away, many stores and a mall very close to the hotel. Very gentle and polite personel, reception 24h. If I come back in Paris, i will choose the same hotel

Nice, clean and comfy hotel situated in a very convenient spot, well served by metro, 30-40 minutes walking distance from some famous and less famous attractions in Paris. Gentle and kind personnel, I would recommend it without hesitation to friends and relative for a relaxing weekend or longer journey in Paris.

This was our first visit to Paris and La Manufacture was like a home away from home. The staff were amazing and the buffet breakfast was great value and tasty. The hotel was clean, well kept and very close to the train station, local shops, cafes, cinema and restaurants. We will stay here again!

I want to give four stars. The room was much smaller than it appeared online. Barely enough room for luggage. But it was clean and comfortable. The staff at the desk was delightful and helpful. They could not have been nicer and more accommodating. I was encouraged at check in to purchase breakfast for two at 25€ so we did. I have celiac (can’t eat wheat) and the damage caused by it makes eating dairy products difficult. The previous night we stayed at a lovely hotel near the airport that had a fabulous breakfast for free, so we tested the suggestion even if it means 24€.
We arrived for breakfast and found a hard boiled egg, cups filled with soggy fruit, few coffee options, tons of bread, e few processed meats, plain yogurt, a few cheeses. I obviously could only eat the egg and the soggy fruit. I noticed on the wall pictures of omelets. But no omelets were offered. I asked the employee if I could maybe have an omelet. She glared at me and loudly blurted out, “Those are not for you!!! You may not have omelets!!!” I was horrified at her attitude and rudeness. I grabbed the hard boiled egg and soggy fruit and sat down to eat it. I was in tears, as the other guests were glaring at me. After I finished the egg and fruit, another employee came out with a omelette on a plate. At that point my stomach was in knots, all I wanted to do was go to my room and escape the glares of the guests and the rude employee who was so condescending.
We still do not know why the employee was so vicious. Maybe because I am American off Hispanic and Indigenous descent? I can’t think of any other reason other than she was racist and disliked us from the start. We were gracious to her and only asked a simple question.
I could not think of going back for another breakfast so I asked for a refund for the following prepaid breakfast. The gentleman at the desk was kind and thoughtful and granted a refund. I am however still waiting for the refund.
My recommendation is DO NOT BUY THE BREAKFAST!! Especially if you are not French. There are plenty of lovely cafes within walking distance.

Dr. C. Livingston

Best in the area. Professional staff, nice location, hip. Best deal around Place d'Italie. Very clean, easy access, nice area, good service. Average boring breakfast; they can improve in that are but there are many cafes in the zone.

Nice hotel, quiet street though nearby metro station and many cafés. Clean rooms and friendly staff. Great value for money. One recommdation for the hotel would be to install power outlets / usb portal around the bedside table. That would greatly improve comfortable stay

This seems like a secret hotel since it’s too good to be true. Stylish lobby and very comfortable rooms. The staff is professional and very friendly. As for the location it is right next to the Place d’Italie with a good shopping mall. Great experience!

I have been to this hotel before just for one night and I had a lively short stay.
It is a beautiful, clean and convenient hotel as it is placed in a nice area of Paris with easy access to transport and also to just walk through the street of Paris.
The hotel has a sweet charm and everyone was very polite always and helpful.
I look forward to my next stay again, hopefully soon!
Thank you.

Great stuff, very welcoming and supportive. Good rooms and spotless clean. There are also many cafes und bakery’s nearbei. We didn’t try the breakfast cause we were always on the way :) We’ll come again. Thanks!

I travel to Paris frequently and found this jewel of a hotel.
I loved it so much I stayed here for a month!
Its location is very safe, in the Le Gobelins area. You have everything right out your front door. There are great cafes, bakeries, grocery stores, and anything you could want or need. The Metro is conveniently one block away to whisk you off anywhere in the city.

The hotel staff was better than most 5-star hotels I've stayed with.
They were always so nice and helpful. They soon became my extended family and truly care about making your stay a great experience.
The front desk employee named Amina went above and beyond.
Every day she would help me with my french as I'm American and certainly needed the extra help.

Don't miss out on the breakfast they offer. It's affordable and you will not find a better buffet anywhere in town.

My daughter will be attending college in Paris. We decided to visit to "check" things out: transportation, neighborhoods, etc, as well as do a little sightseeing.

Hotel La Manufacture was the perfect HQ for our trip. Well positioned to use all types of public transportation: Metro, Bus, RER, and walking. Safe neighborhood for my daughter and her friend to go out alone. Great restaurants, pharmacies. stores etc. all reasonably priced. The staff was very helpful. The breakfast was delicious. The rooms were clean and cute. We will return in August!

Small but very cosy hotel, in a very good location with very kind staff. The bedroom was clean and cosy and the bed very comfortable. The atmosphere is calm and welcoming. If you are looking for a quiet and beautiful place, lt’s the perfect one! Thank you!

Lovely hotel, clean and extremely comfertable, staff and wellcoming and helpful. Breakfast was excellent with a good choice.Just a two minute walk from Place d'italie metro and in a great area with plenty of bars,bistros and restaurants (would recommend Restaurant Marty) and shopping.

Nice place. Near metro station. Quiet street. The room was little but comfortable. Good bed. Clean bathroom. Good service. We used the rental bikes nearby. We had a very nice stay and we will return again

Excellent hotel, clean, comfortable, friendly and in an ideal part of Paris. They offer a very good breakfast. I have stayed in this hotel over the years and it always remains of a high standard. Being close to Place d’Italie makes it an ideal location.

We will be back at La Manufacture. During our 4 days stay in Paris we have experienced great hospitality. The friendly staff were very willing to organize a great birthday experience for me and my family.

We requested a room with a balcony, for which we paid extra, yet the room we've been assigned to did not have a balcony. After we raised this, we were moved into a room directly below and it had a teeny tiny corner balcony where you could fit one chair and a tiny table - hardly a balcony that could be used by a couple - I appreciate balconies in France are small, but I could see a few rooms with bigger ones which we could have been assigned. We were not offered anything to make up for the mistake.

Overall the stay was alright however not worth the money. The room was very small as well, just a bed and a bathroom essentially. We specifically went for a mid range price rather than a cheaper option to have a better standard however I believe we overpaid for what we got.

Firstly, positives - this place is fairly affordable, rooms are adequate and absolutely no problems with decor or anything broken or anything like that. All worked as expected.

The location is really good actually - I was a bit worried that it looked so far from everything in central Paris on the map, but actually it's in a nice area that's a minute's walk from the metro station - the station is linked by three different lines, so you can quickly get anywhere you want to in Paris in no more than 30 mins. The immediate area is really nice too, though it seems more a place that locals live than a place for tourists (that's not a negative at all). But if you want your more 'touristy' bars and restaurants then there's some about 10 min walk away towards Austerlitz, and also it's not far from the Latin Quarter. There's a huge shopping mall near the hotel too which was really handy. All in all, I loved the area and would consider staying here again.

However, I'm not 100% sure I'd stay at La Manufacture though - the rooms were much smaller than expected, even though we ordered the Double Rooms which were supposed to be spacier. Bathroom is similarly tight. It's perfectly manageable as a couple, and we stayed for 5 nights, but it's not a room size I'd choose to stay in again. Though one positive was a balcony which was nice, but not something to take advantage of in February.

Service was ok, they were helpful with things like ironing boards and general directions, but we had some language barrier issues a fair bit (when we asked for local things to do, or about the metro cards), which shouldn't be an issue as we should learn better French, but something that had an impact. Also, I had a perfume bottle go missing and it was a bit difficult to explain things and other staff members weren't told about it (so I had to keep repeating the issue to staff).

Overall, I'd say if this hotel works for your price point, go for it. Expect small rooms but unless you plan to spend all your time in Paris in a hotel room, it's more than fine. But if you're travelling around Paris most days then this is a great place to embark from and explore the city, as well as a great local area for bars, cafes and supermarkets.

Super clean and tidy,1 minute away from the metro station and private parking on foot,close to mall,supermarket,cafes,bakery and restaurants.
Receptionists and staff very kind and helpful.
Ideal choice for every occasion.

We were in Paris for 4 days and after staying near the Eiffel tower, we planned to stay for 2 days at La Manufacture. This is a very heritage-looking hotel right next to Place d'Italie. The location is perfect with buses and metro just 1 min away. The staff of the hotel was really nice and helpful. The rooms are very good, slightly smaller but good. We were offered an upgrade but we have to let go of the balcony. We did not take it but it was really nice of the hotel to offer.

Overall, totally recommended !!

The Hotel was easy to reach with the Metro. The staff was very friendly and knowledgable. The rooms were cozy and clean, and the shower had great water pressure. The Breakfast buffet offered everything that one could need for a good start in the day. I would deffinitly stay here again.

We stayed in the hotel for 4 nights while visiting Paris and I have to say it was the perfect choice! It’s super close to the metro and bus so it’s very easy getting anywhere in the city, plus you can also walk to the city centre which won’t take you more than half an hour. There’s also lots of restaurants and supermarkets around which is great if you don’t want to go too far to get some dinner. The hotel is very well priced and is also super clean, although the room might be a bit small it’s the perfect size for two people. The staff was very nice and welcoming, they also helped keep our luggage the last day because our plane back home was leaving very early. We’re super happy about our stay at hotel la manufacture and we’ll definitely be back soon!

Everything was really good, hotel is clean and staff friendly. They have 24 hours service in the reception. Located next to a metro station. Would stay again if I need to go to Paris for a short trip.

Lovely, welcoming and clean stay. All you would need for a city break to Paris! Room was not cramped and it was nice to have a balcony, even if it was tiny as it felt very Parisian☺️ receptionists were all very willing to answer questions about the area and the metro.
Nice area too and very close to a metro stop so transport was very easy!

The staff was very friendly and the rooms were tidy and spacious. Great value for money! I would certainly recommend this hotel to anyone! I've been to many Parisian hotels and I've rarely found rooms this clean and staff this helpful.

Very fair prices, clean rooms, kind staff at reception. Very close to Metro (Place d'Italie, Campo Formio) and amenities (super market, nice restaurants and bars). The rooms are equipped with electric kettle and the hotel provides for instant coffee, sugar and milk portions. This allows you to make a decent coffee before starting your day. There is also the option of buying breakfast at the hotel for 12E/person/day. All in all, we found the hotel a real value-for-money not far from tourist attractions.

I have stayed here at least five times. I love coming down in the morning to the breakfast buffet. The staff are always very sweet and hospitable. The place is also very clean, and in a quite neighborhood which i like, very easy to get to when youre ridding the train all day.

Beautiful hotel. Great service team are excellent especially Amina at reception helps with everything you need breakfast was great rooms are very clean Thanks to Amina she was excellent and very helpful

This hotels acommodations were average at best. however, the staff were really nice and the service was good. If I should return, I would opt for one of the rooms on the 7th floor. Sadly they’re a bit expensive.

Hotel located in an excellent position, outside the chaos of the center but still in an area full of shops and restaurants. One step away from all the attractions of Paris thanks to the metro and bus stops. Completely renovated, welcoming, clean and with an excellent breakfast. Staff courteous and very helpful. We will definitely be back!

Visited on 12th November, 2019, though late for the review. Very beautiful room and decor. Balcony view was awesome and one of the best thing of the trip, especially the night view. Sometimes you just need to enjoy your own company, hence it was the last solo trip before pandemic.

Our stay at the Manufacture Hotel was perfect. The staff was very friendly and helpfull. The room was very cosy and super clean. Great location, near metro and only 30 min. walking distance to Pantheon and La Cite. It was wonderfull time in Paris.

The location of the hotel is very good, 200m from metro stadion Place d'Italie., you can walk 30 min to Latin quarter, Sorbonne, Pantheon, Seine, Louvre...the lobby and the staff of the hotel are very nice.We did not get the room with the balcony eventhough we made a reservation for it. Our room was small and lots of the furniture needs to be renovated. The tv remote control did not work. The heating was not on, I need to start it on my own. The bed was great, we slept like babies after whole Day of sightseeing.I think that hotel is a little bit to expensive for the facility that provides.

A short city trip in Paris ,
Perfect location , Nice bedroom and bathroom . Breakfast also very correct .
Of i would-be have to come back in Paris wil choose the same place again !
Parking facilities nearby as wel

We had a very pleasant stay in Hotel la Manufacture. Room was clean and the bed was good. The 13th is a very nice neighbourhood, and the Place d'Italie is a convenient public transport hub. Would visit again!

Really nice rooms, fantastic beds and pillows, very helpful staff. One of the few hotels where the rooms are nicer than the lobby!

It was our 10-year anniversary trip and they upgraded us (without us asking) to the only room in the hotel with a view of the Eiffel Tower. Plus my wife was pregnant and they were happy to let us store in the fridge in the the bar any particular foods or drinks she wanted to hand to ease her morning sickness.

Place d'Italie is obviously not next door to "all the sights", but it's an un-touristy area with lots of excellent, well-priced restaurants within an easy walk.

Much recommended.

Very clean and pleasant hotel, small but well-appointed room. The one thing lacking is a mini-fridge: I enjoy buying myself a bottle of something and keeping it fresh which is impossible here. Otherwise impeccably clean, pleasant and cozy room. Very comfy bed. Very cheap for the quality provided.

The hotel staff upgraded our room because this was our first time in Paris. We were on the seventh floor and had a great room with two windows and a large bathroom. We left the hotel in the morning and did not return until night time and did not try the breakfast. The room was always very clean. The staff even folded one of our own blankets for us. The hotel is perfectly situated by a Metro and bus station, grocery stores, cafes, and a shopping center.

We enjoy our stay at the hotel. We had the top level room under the hood. A cosy small room with everything. The bathroom was clean (although a small long hair on the floor) and up-to-date. We walked to the center of Paris, but transport is nearby. Lovely location. We will certainly come back, although the price was quite high.

It was the best Trip ever! Thank you so much for the free upgrade!!!! When we will travel again to Paris, we will always take your hotel. You are able to be in 20 minutes in the city, perfect for a nice holiday in Paris!

We had a great time at La Manufacture -nice area, lots of cute restaurants just after Place d'Italie, easy to reach and super walkable. Safe, clean, everyone was happy to help and make our stay comfortable -not a single bad word to say!

We have been here 4 nights the bank holidays of October 2021.
The hotel is very well located, close to the Italy square, with lots of restaurants and cafes in the area. The rooms are small but nice and very comfortable and we are not in París to stay in the room, so they are perfect.
The staff speaks English very well and they are always ready to help.
Perfect hotel for a weekend if you want to visit the city.

This is the perfect spot, it had everything I needed - the bed was super comfortable, superb location, super clean and cute. I could not ask for more. And great price!! The staff was super helpful and courteous while at the same time respecting privacy.

We had an amazing stay at the hotel! The staff was very friendly and the room was perfect for a city trip. It is quite small but contains everything you need. Especially the location close to restaurants and a big metro station was a plus!

Bathrooms smell like mildew/mold. No fridge. Suitcase barely fits on the ground because the room is so small. You took a deposit and then a separate payment??? So now we've double paid and I'm waiting for deposit back. Never had a hotel do that before and it's really frustrating.

I have recently been at the hotel. It is very charming, in a nice building and in a nice area at a walking distance from the hystorical center. Rooms are nice and confortable. The staff of the reception is always nice to solve any issue and give you the best tips for your journey in Paris.

Our stay at the Hotel La Manufacture was fantastic! The staff were so kind and helpful, truly were very accommodating and sweet! The rooms were clean, although slightly small, but I felt very satisfied with this place especially for the price. Will be coming again!

Hotel La Manufacture is pleasant hotel. I had a room facing the courtyard, which was very calm. It is centrally located, and the staff is friendly and helpful. The beds are very comfortable too. I would happily come back another time.

Just a great hotel that offers your basic hotel needs. The rooms provide a nice bed with a good shower. The location of the hotel at the Place d’Italie is great. There are many nice restaurants in the neighbourhood and the connections with the metro lines are also great.
